1
00:00:01,640 --> 00:00:04,310
You'll bring that woman to our house?

2
00:00:04,510 --> 00:00:06,010
Watch how you address her!

3
00:00:06,310 --> 00:00:09,010
Do you want me to say she's my stepmother?

4
00:00:09,750 --> 00:00:11,150
Why are you doing this?

5
00:00:11,850 --> 00:00:13,220
What about you?

6
00:00:14,150 --> 00:00:16,090
I know how much you want my title,

7
00:00:16,590 --> 00:00:18,860
but how dare
you harm the company to get it?

8
00:00:19,790 --> 00:00:21,090
What are you talking about?

9
00:00:21,360 --> 00:00:22,530
Your brother, Ji Seop.

10
00:00:22,930 --> 00:00:25,100
If he lost his shares
for sabotaging the business,

11
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:27,300
you were going to take it all.
Do you think I wouldn't catch on?

12
00:00:27,970 --> 00:00:30,400
That's why you egged on that moron!

13
00:00:30,700 --> 00:00:33,100
So you could take his shares
and then take me on!

14
00:00:33,470 --> 00:00:36,040
Who told you that? Was it that woman?

15
00:00:36,510 --> 00:00:38,580
Are you yelling at me
because of what she said?

16
00:00:39,510 --> 00:00:41,010
Get a hold of yourself.

17
00:00:41,210 --> 00:00:43,350
Don't fall for a vixen...

18
00:00:43,380 --> 00:00:45,780
who's trying to get between us!

19
00:00:46,920 --> 00:00:48,290
How dare you?

20
00:01:16,380 --> 00:01:17,650
Watching Kyung Chae...

21
00:01:18,220 --> 00:01:20,690
lie about everything to our father...

22
00:01:20,690 --> 00:01:22,690
made me so angry.

23
00:01:22,720 --> 00:01:25,590
Why did you sign the letter of indemnity?

24
00:01:27,290 --> 00:01:29,660
It was the only way
to make sure Father would trust me.

25
00:01:30,130 --> 00:01:33,730
The sly fox knew you'd bring
a fake contract and made you...

26
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:36,300
sign that thing so you'd take the blame.

27
00:01:36,570 --> 00:01:38,240
What will you do now?

28
00:01:38,370 --> 00:01:41,310
He wanted me gone. He said I was fired.

29
00:01:42,170 --> 00:01:45,080
I'm sick of the place.
I don't want to work there.

30
00:01:45,910 --> 00:01:48,450
I'll be jobless for a while.

31
00:01:50,650 --> 00:01:52,080
This is insane.

32
00:01:53,020 --> 00:01:55,690
Will you let Kyung Chae
get away with this?

33
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:59,690
You got fired.
You might as well take her on.

34
00:02:08,270 --> 00:02:09,730
I hope it doesn't scar.

35
00:02:12,300 --> 00:02:13,910
What happened?

36
00:02:14,140 --> 00:02:15,570
This has never happened before
since I got hired.

37
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:19,610
The chairman has a fiery temper,
but he never treated you like this.

38
00:02:23,150 --> 00:02:24,420
It's such an upsetting sight.

39
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:28,120
How could the chairman do this to you?

40
00:02:28,390 --> 00:02:30,490
What wouldn't he do
if he's crazy about a woman?

41
00:02:31,920 --> 00:02:33,190
What do you mean?

42
00:02:33,730 --> 00:02:35,090
He's seeing someone.

43
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:37,430
She works at Mingang.

44
00:02:37,660 --> 00:02:38,660
What?

45
00:02:40,270 --> 00:02:41,600
There's more to the story.

46
00:02:42,470 --> 00:02:43,540
That woman...

47
00:02:44,870 --> 00:02:46,270
is the same age as me.

48
00:02:47,510 --> 00:02:48,570
My gosh.

49
00:02:57,920 --> 00:02:59,680
Is my smart CEO sister home?

50
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:03,350
Keep it down. Ms. Kyung Chae
is in a bad mood right now.

51
00:03:04,490 --> 00:03:06,590
I'm in a bad mood myself!

52
00:03:07,730 --> 00:03:08,760
But...

53
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:17,700
Min Kyung Chae. Come out here.

54
00:03:19,570 --> 00:03:21,210
Didn't you hear me?

55
00:03:28,580 --> 00:03:31,720
Let's be honest.
Don't you think you should...

56
00:03:31,820 --> 00:03:33,820
at least apologize to me?

57
00:03:34,550 --> 00:03:36,620
Whose fault is it that I got fired?

58
00:03:36,890 --> 00:03:39,060
If you had a drink,
go to your room and sleep it off.

59
00:03:39,290 --> 00:03:41,560
You can't do this to me!

60
00:03:42,090 --> 00:03:44,660
I'd let it slide if you were Soo Jung,

61
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:46,430
but we're full siblings.

62
00:03:46,630 --> 00:03:49,170
You stabbed me in the back,

63
00:03:49,170 --> 00:03:51,170
and that's immoral. Do you get it?

64
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:53,300
Take it up with our father.

65
00:03:53,910 --> 00:03:56,270
He's the one who distrusts you the most.

66
00:04:02,810 --> 00:04:04,280
You wait and see.

67
00:04:06,850 --> 00:04:10,390
At the crucial moment,
see which sister I side with.

68
00:04:15,490 --> 00:04:16,490
My gosh.

69
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:24,040
Where's Kyung Chae?

70
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:25,370
She left early in the morning.

71
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:26,600
Goodness.

72
00:04:28,940 --> 00:04:30,840
Don't think of coming to the office again.

73
00:04:31,610 --> 00:04:33,650
Be grateful I didn't disown you.

74
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:35,480
Okay.

75
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:29,430
(Mingang Distribution)

76
00:05:42,550 --> 00:05:44,650
Do you have more luck than competence?

77
00:05:45,250 --> 00:05:46,920
You survive each and every crisis.

78
00:05:48,390 --> 00:05:50,490
I'm sorry if that's how you view me.

79
00:05:50,820 --> 00:05:52,260
I did the best I could.

80
00:05:52,820 --> 00:05:54,730
I guess that wasn't good enough for you.

81
00:05:55,490 --> 00:05:57,160
Now you even talk back.

82
00:05:57,730 --> 00:05:59,900
You used to be humble at least.

83
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:03,600
I'm surrounded by people who want me gone.

84
00:06:03,900 --> 00:06:06,040
I decided I couldn't afford to be humble.

85
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:09,270
So you'll say whatever you want,
even if it's unwelcome advice?

86
00:06:10,610 --> 00:06:11,910
That's not what I meant.

87
00:06:13,610 --> 00:06:15,280
You and I are incompatible.

88
00:06:16,010 --> 00:06:17,480
I had high hopes for you at one time.

89
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:22,750
(Mingang Distribution)

90
00:06:27,490 --> 00:06:28,490
Just a moment.

91
00:06:45,080 --> 00:06:46,140
Going up.

92
00:06:46,710 --> 00:06:47,880
The doors are closing.

93
00:06:53,250 --> 00:06:54,490
Do you have plans this evening?

94
00:06:59,620 --> 00:07:00,890
Not really.

95
00:07:01,830 --> 00:07:04,800
Then join me for dinner.
I have something to say too.

96
00:07:05,660 --> 00:07:07,670
You said you'd be responsible,
and you should be.

97
00:07:17,840 --> 00:07:19,440
What was that about?

98
00:07:20,280 --> 00:07:21,280
Shall I not ask?

99
00:07:22,650 --> 00:07:25,180
Do I not have the right
to ask you anything?

100
00:07:31,090 --> 00:07:32,820
I don't know how this might sound.

101
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:37,330
I'm worried about how close
you're getting with the chairman.

102
00:07:38,430 --> 00:07:40,670
I know what you're worried about,
Director.

103
00:07:40,900 --> 00:07:42,730
I'm not talking as your director.

104
00:07:43,630 --> 00:07:45,270
I'm talking as Moon Tae Kyung, the man.

105
00:07:47,770 --> 00:07:49,340
- Director.
- I know.

106
00:07:50,510 --> 00:07:53,380
I know you don't do something
unless you have a reason.

107
00:07:53,710 --> 00:07:55,110
You must have a reason for doing this.

108
00:07:55,580 --> 00:07:57,220
Like how I had a reason to join Mingang.

109
00:07:57,920 --> 00:07:59,150
Ms. Lucia.

110
00:08:00,220 --> 00:08:02,350
Don't take a path
with an obvious dead end.

111
00:08:04,690 --> 00:08:06,990
What if you must go all the way
to see what happens?

112
00:08:07,260 --> 00:08:08,860
Whatever choice you make,

113
00:08:09,990 --> 00:08:11,760
you will lose something.

114
00:08:12,060 --> 00:08:14,700
If I make a choice despite that,
that will be because...

115
00:08:16,070 --> 00:08:19,270
I want something so desperately
that I'm willing to take the chance.

116
00:08:31,420 --> 00:08:33,750
Did you leave
at the crack of dawn to avoid me?

117
00:08:35,150 --> 00:08:38,120
Why did you cut your hair?
Are you protesting?

118
00:08:40,930 --> 00:08:42,860
Wouldn't it be nice to go with the flow?

119
00:08:42,860 --> 00:08:44,730
Why fight for something you can't have?

120
00:08:45,060 --> 00:08:46,130
"Go with the flow?"

121
00:08:47,060 --> 00:08:48,900
Since when did you allow
just anyone into our house?

122
00:08:50,330 --> 00:08:53,840
Despite her best efforts,
you never let Soo Jung's mother move in.

123
00:08:56,610 --> 00:08:57,680
Our house.

124
00:08:58,580 --> 00:09:01,110
It was my late mother's dream house.

125
00:09:01,850 --> 00:09:03,310
You were busy at work,

126
00:09:03,510 --> 00:09:07,050
so she picked out every brick
and every pane of glass.

127
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:08,850
She built the house
she wanted to grow old in.

128
00:09:10,590 --> 00:09:12,160
She just died before her time.

129
00:09:15,990 --> 00:09:17,030
Lucia.

130
00:09:18,330 --> 00:09:20,100
Be satisfied with the fact
that you made her yours.

131
00:09:23,730 --> 00:09:25,800
(Mingang Distribution)

132
00:09:27,310 --> 00:09:28,310
My gosh.

133
00:09:29,410 --> 00:09:30,410
You got hurt?

134
00:09:30,410 --> 00:09:32,440
(CEO Min Kyung Chae)

135
00:09:34,180 --> 00:09:35,810
Did that woman cause...

136
00:09:35,810 --> 00:09:37,210
Who else do we have issues with?

137
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:41,190
You should go.
The chairman wants to see you.

138
00:09:44,560 --> 00:09:46,920
Why haven't you approved
the contract Lucia brought us?

139
00:09:47,890 --> 00:09:50,460
I don't think Legal can sign off on it.

140
00:09:50,700 --> 00:09:51,700
Why not?

141
00:09:51,930 --> 00:09:54,270
You know how one-sided the conditions are.

142
00:09:54,370 --> 00:09:56,570
So what? We have no other choice.

143
00:09:56,670 --> 00:09:58,170
Sign off on it and move forward.

144
00:09:58,640 --> 00:10:00,500
How much do you trust Ms. Lucia?

145
00:10:01,710 --> 00:10:02,910
What does that mean?

146
00:10:03,610 --> 00:10:05,310
Is Kyung Chae rubbing off on you?

147
00:10:05,680 --> 00:10:06,910
I'm not being negative.

148
00:10:08,010 --> 00:10:10,510
I don't understand how someone like you
could trust her so completely.

149
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:12,280
There's no way I can't trust her.

150
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:14,550
She comes to the rescue
whenever the company is in peril.

151
00:10:14,990 --> 00:10:16,920
But Ms. Min is so against the idea.

152
00:10:17,050 --> 00:10:19,820
She has much more to learn
when it comes to judging people.

153
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:23,330
Why can't she trust Lucia
when what you see is what you get?

154
00:10:30,100 --> 00:10:33,070
He won't see the knife
until it stabs him in the back.

155
00:10:34,770 --> 00:10:38,680
You don't know why Sul Hee came here
and what she wants,

156
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:40,380
you stupid old man.

157
00:10:46,550 --> 00:10:47,720
Hello.

158
00:10:49,620 --> 00:10:51,860
Here's the lunchbox
the youngest daughter ordered.

159
00:10:53,060 --> 00:10:54,990
We ask too much of you.

160
00:10:57,160 --> 00:10:58,200
Is that the lunchbox?

161
00:10:59,030 --> 00:11:01,830
- I'm going out.
- Where to?

162
00:11:01,900 --> 00:11:03,100
Who is this for?

163
00:11:03,330 --> 00:11:04,900
It's for someone special.

164
00:11:05,040 --> 00:11:07,770
It's not someone
who claims to be your birth mom, is it?

165
00:11:08,740 --> 00:11:09,810
No.

166
00:11:14,980 --> 00:11:17,280
It looks like
she's off to see someone nice.

167
00:11:30,430 --> 00:11:31,600
Hi, Se Ri.

168
00:11:31,860 --> 00:11:33,060
I'm in the lobby.

169
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:35,730
Can you come downstairs?

170
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,070
To the lobby?

171
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:57,920
What are you doing here?

172
00:11:59,020 --> 00:12:00,160
Are you here to see me?

173
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:06,000
What did you just hide?

174
00:12:12,070 --> 00:12:13,300
Who is this for?

175
00:12:14,910 --> 00:12:16,140
Is it for Lucia?

176
00:12:21,150 --> 00:12:22,350
What are you doing?

177
00:12:24,180 --> 00:12:25,180
Kyung Chae!

178
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:28,090
You came here to see her
with a packed lunchbox?

179
00:12:28,450 --> 00:12:31,660
Why? Have you fallen for her,
just like our father?

180
00:12:31,660 --> 00:12:35,090
You don't know what this is about.
I owe her, and that's why I'm doing this!

181
00:12:35,090 --> 00:12:36,990
Since when did you care
about owing others?

182
00:12:37,560 --> 00:12:38,730
Go home!

183
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:47,940
How dare you treat my visitor like this?

184
00:13:01,450 --> 00:13:03,220
Don't be like this already.

185
00:13:03,920 --> 00:13:07,320
Pretty soon, your sister
will play dead if I tell her to.

186
00:13:11,230 --> 00:13:13,600
(Chunbokjib Black Goat)

187
00:13:15,570 --> 00:13:17,670
Number 27, please come in.

188
00:13:17,900 --> 00:13:20,740
- This is your table.
- Welcome.

189
00:13:22,070 --> 00:13:23,310
You can sit here.

190
00:13:23,310 --> 00:13:25,110
- And you here.
- Thanks.

191
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:29,650
Dear valued customers.
Nothing is more important than our health.

192
00:13:29,810 --> 00:13:32,620
Health equals money,
and it also equals making money.

193
00:13:32,620 --> 00:13:35,150
You're making money by eating our food.

194
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:38,390
Enjoy the goat soup and become rich.

195
00:13:38,390 --> 00:13:40,590
- Excuse me.
- Yes. I'm Oh Pan Sool,

196
00:13:40,590 --> 00:13:43,930
and I look to be 29
because I only ate what was good for me.

197
00:13:43,930 --> 00:13:45,160
Can I help you?

198
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:47,400
Do you have anything for children?

199
00:13:47,970 --> 00:13:50,530
We do. We have a whole list of that.

200
00:13:51,340 --> 00:13:54,070
Take a look and order all you'd like.

201
00:13:56,110 --> 00:13:57,470
Hey, there are lots of customers.

202
00:13:58,940 --> 00:14:00,040
Father?

203
00:14:00,540 --> 00:14:02,350
- Hello.
- Mom, Dad.

204
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:05,580
Why are you here
when you should be at work?

205
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:12,360
So your father did this?

206
00:14:14,190 --> 00:14:15,330
Is that it?

207
00:14:16,060 --> 00:14:17,090
Yes.

208
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,330
Have some soup.

209
00:14:19,460 --> 00:14:22,600
You'll need something to soothe
your stomach if you drank all night.

210
00:14:32,210 --> 00:14:34,110
This is so nice and refreshing.

211
00:14:35,950 --> 00:14:38,350
We served some other things too.
Try them all.

212
00:14:41,790 --> 00:14:44,760
He might feel bad for you later on.

213
00:14:44,820 --> 00:14:47,690
Do you think he'll call you back?

214
00:14:49,930 --> 00:14:51,060
- My gosh.
- Hey, don't.

215
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:54,900
I know the food is good,
but stop eating and start talking.

216
00:14:54,900 --> 00:14:56,100
Were you starved?

217
00:14:56,300 --> 00:14:57,840
Ja Kyung. Or my beautiful wife.

218
00:14:57,840 --> 00:15:00,970
My fingers keep curling into a fist.
Will you straighten them for me?

219
00:15:01,070 --> 00:15:02,770
- You...
- Stop it.

220
00:15:03,070 --> 00:15:04,140
Here.

221
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:22,890
(Public telephone)

222
00:15:23,030 --> 00:15:25,600
I'll die before my time
if I don't do something.

223
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:27,360
Let's see...

224
00:15:30,430 --> 00:15:33,840
(Director Moon Tae Kyung)

225
00:15:38,110 --> 00:15:39,110
Hello?

226
00:15:39,840 --> 00:15:41,450
Is that Moon Tae Kyung's phone?

227
00:15:41,710 --> 00:15:43,550
Yes, speaking. Who's this?

228
00:15:44,650 --> 00:15:46,780
It's Jo Pil Doo.

229
00:15:49,490 --> 00:15:52,190
I was afraid you'd changed your number.

230
00:15:54,020 --> 00:15:57,130
Do you think we could meet up today?

231
00:15:58,230 --> 00:15:59,260
Yes, sure.

232
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:01,200
I'll come over after work.

233
00:16:10,840 --> 00:16:13,110
(Samcheonri Briquette)

234
00:16:18,880 --> 00:16:22,420
Aren't you worried
I might disappear again?

235
00:16:22,620 --> 00:16:23,920
Why wouldn't I worry?

236
00:16:24,590 --> 00:16:27,420
I'm thinking of tying you up right now
so you can't run away.

237
00:16:28,030 --> 00:16:29,230
You would.

238
00:16:32,460 --> 00:16:34,400
I'm at your mercy.

239
00:16:34,870 --> 00:16:36,370
I know what I did wrong.

240
00:16:36,530 --> 00:16:39,270
Why didn't you go
where I'd never find you?

241
00:16:39,270 --> 00:16:40,640
Why did you call me?

242
00:16:41,610 --> 00:16:43,610
I never slept peacefully...

243
00:16:43,610 --> 00:16:45,940
a day in my life because of Min Doo Sik.

244
00:16:46,280 --> 00:16:47,810
He chases me even in my dreams.

245
00:16:48,680 --> 00:16:49,850
Do you think...

246
00:16:50,380 --> 00:16:54,150
you could take me in and keep me safe?

247
00:16:55,350 --> 00:16:56,820
I live on the street,

248
00:16:56,820 --> 00:16:59,420
and he might kill me without a trace.

249
00:17:01,590 --> 00:17:04,030
I know I shouldn't, but I called you...

250
00:17:04,030 --> 00:17:05,900
because I had no other option.

251
00:17:11,340 --> 00:17:13,240
I enjoyed our last meal together.

252
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:15,070
What will you buy me this time?

253
00:17:16,340 --> 00:17:17,880
We can eat a bit later.

254
00:17:21,410 --> 00:17:23,550
Take this first.

255
00:17:27,990 --> 00:17:30,690
Did you think I'd call you my girlfriend
and not do anything else?

256
00:17:31,720 --> 00:17:32,760
Open it.

257
00:17:44,840 --> 00:17:46,740
It belonged to my late wife.

258
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:56,710
Hello, Chairman Jung.

259
00:17:58,350 --> 00:18:00,720
I'm still looking into that.

260
00:18:01,520 --> 00:18:03,190
There aren't any issues.

261
00:18:35,650 --> 00:18:37,350
I can't help it if you don't want it.

262
00:18:38,520 --> 00:18:40,890
I didn't think you'd reject it right away.

263
00:18:51,540 --> 00:18:53,100
You scared me.

264
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:56,210
No one has ever kept me on my toes
the way you do.

265
00:18:56,710 --> 00:18:58,110
Were you nervous?

266
00:18:58,480 --> 00:19:00,010
You almost had me.

267
00:19:00,610 --> 00:19:02,110
I was worried you'd say no.

268
00:19:04,550 --> 00:19:05,820
Why would I?

269
00:19:06,620 --> 00:19:08,250
I'm yours now.

270
00:19:13,820 --> 00:19:17,330
Did you find out anything else
while working at Mingang?

271
00:19:19,930 --> 00:19:21,000
No.

272
00:19:21,030 --> 00:19:23,400
Why not hire someone to mess him up?

273
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:25,770
Why are you just watching what happens?

274
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:28,510
It's not personal revenge I'm after.

275
00:19:29,070 --> 00:19:31,640
I want Min Doo Sik
to pay for his crimes in court...

276
00:19:32,240 --> 00:19:34,280
so my parents can be cleared.

277
00:19:36,210 --> 00:19:38,420
I'll quit drinking and go to rehab.

278
00:19:38,550 --> 00:19:41,080
When I become a credible witness,

279
00:19:41,080 --> 00:19:42,490
I'll testify in court.

280
00:19:46,620 --> 00:19:49,390
Do you think you could take me in...

281
00:19:50,760 --> 00:19:52,200
until then?

282
00:19:58,600 --> 00:20:00,470
The design is outdated,

283
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:02,410
but it'll cost a lot
because it's a real diamond.

284
00:20:03,810 --> 00:20:05,480
It's how you feel that's more important.

285
00:20:06,210 --> 00:20:08,080
Where did you get the idea
to give me this?

286
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:11,180
Most men don't care enough about details.

287
00:20:12,020 --> 00:20:13,580
I'm pretty sensitive like that.

288
00:20:17,050 --> 00:20:18,460
I'll come clean.

289
00:20:19,460 --> 00:20:21,060
Soo Jung told me what to do.

290
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:30,570
If you've made up your mind,
you must make it known to her.

291
00:20:30,930 --> 00:20:33,570
Women don't like men
who are nothing but talk.

292
00:20:33,670 --> 00:20:36,140
- What are you talking about?
- I'm talking about Lucia.

293
00:20:36,410 --> 00:20:39,410
Give her a ring
if you want to call her yours.

294
00:20:39,410 --> 00:20:40,980
You'll just call her that?

295
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:43,180
I'm too old
to go around shopping for a ring.

296
00:20:43,350 --> 00:20:45,080
Don't get one at a random store.

297
00:20:45,480 --> 00:20:47,680
They don't mean anything.

298
00:20:49,650 --> 00:20:53,360
Your late wife's ring.
I think that would work.

299
00:20:54,460 --> 00:20:57,030
Lucia deserves that ring.

300
00:20:57,330 --> 00:21:00,730
She saved you and Se Ri.
You could give her something better.

301
00:21:01,970 --> 00:21:04,770
I think she's charming, and I'm a woman.

302
00:21:05,040 --> 00:21:07,300
I'd fall for her if I were a man.

303
00:21:08,170 --> 00:21:10,910
Don't lose her and regret it later.
Grab her while you can.

304
00:21:13,310 --> 00:21:15,480
Will you do as I say from now on?

305
00:21:18,680 --> 00:21:19,980
Why won't you answer?

306
00:21:22,450 --> 00:21:24,150
We took the long way round...

307
00:21:25,060 --> 00:21:26,790
when there was a shortcut.

308
00:21:27,790 --> 00:21:29,930
I was afraid I'd appear senile,

309
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:32,330
so I hid how I felt and lied about it.

310
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:35,700
I won't do that anymore.

311
00:21:51,680 --> 00:21:52,750
What's this?

312
00:21:54,050 --> 00:21:55,090
Is it...

313
00:21:56,990 --> 00:21:58,520
Did he propose?

314
00:21:59,690 --> 00:22:00,920
It belonged to his late wife.

315
00:22:01,660 --> 00:22:03,760
Then it means even more.

316
00:22:04,230 --> 00:22:06,030
Where did he get the idea?

317
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:08,400
Min Soo Jung coached him.

318
00:22:08,630 --> 00:22:10,300
She did us a great favor.

319
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:14,100
I'm afraid of what she'd do to you
later on, though.

320
00:22:14,710 --> 00:22:18,680
We must make them fight each other
before any of them comes after us.

321
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:21,040
I did some digging.

322
00:22:21,180 --> 00:22:23,850
The board members are staunch protectors
of Min Kyung Chae.

323
00:22:24,410 --> 00:22:28,390
Once I become a non-executiveÂ director,
I'll meet and befriend them,

324
00:22:28,650 --> 00:22:31,150
but if something were to happen,

325
00:22:31,220 --> 00:22:34,120
they'd be willing to vote in her favor.

326
00:22:34,760 --> 00:22:37,660
Does that mean
she'll succeed the chairman?

327
00:22:38,460 --> 00:22:39,930
We can't allow that.

328
00:22:39,930 --> 00:22:44,000
Baek Sul Hee should take over Mingang,
not Min Kyung Chae.

329
00:22:44,370 --> 00:22:45,800
That's only fair.

330
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:48,040
They must lose something precious too.

331
00:22:49,170 --> 00:22:51,880
It boils down to whether
we can control the board.

332
00:22:52,140 --> 00:22:56,180
Every one of them has issues
with women, money, or kids.

333
00:22:56,450 --> 00:22:57,910
No one is squeaky clean.

334
00:22:58,280 --> 00:23:00,820
Min Kyung Chae
solves all their problems for them.

335
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:04,420
They'll be extra tight
if that's how involved they are.

336
00:23:04,690 --> 00:23:06,290
That won't last.

337
00:23:06,420 --> 00:23:09,760
I just have to dangle
something more alluring in front of them.

338
00:23:31,410 --> 00:23:33,050
Is that why you called?

339
00:23:33,750 --> 00:23:35,750
How could I not call when I was worried?

340
00:23:35,790 --> 00:23:38,560
You were humiliated in the lobby
with people watching.

341
00:23:40,190 --> 00:23:42,660
Were you really worried about me?

342
00:23:42,790 --> 00:23:46,460
I was. A wounded heart
hurts more than a wounded body.

343
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:48,400
What if your ego took a hit?

344
00:23:48,470 --> 00:23:50,500
You'd lose self-respect in no time.

345
00:23:51,230 --> 00:23:53,600
Why are you different from other people?

346
00:23:56,140 --> 00:23:57,270
What do you mean?

347
00:23:57,870 --> 00:24:00,710
Other people ask for money
around this time.

348
00:24:01,810 --> 00:24:04,480
That's what the woman
who said she was my mom did as well.

349
00:24:05,750 --> 00:24:07,920
You saved my life.

350
00:24:08,490 --> 00:24:09,790
Not once but twice.

351
00:24:11,220 --> 00:24:13,920
My dad would give you
all the money you want if you asked.

352
00:24:22,470 --> 00:24:25,240
You're more precious than money.

353
00:24:27,370 --> 00:24:29,110
I'm precious?

354
00:24:31,580 --> 00:24:32,610
Then...

355
00:24:33,640 --> 00:24:35,680
did you mean what you said?

356
00:24:36,350 --> 00:24:38,650
You told the man not to touch me
because I was your daughter.

357
00:24:40,420 --> 00:24:41,990
You said you were my mom.

358
00:24:42,420 --> 00:24:44,590
How could I say that if I didn't mean it?

359
00:24:45,460 --> 00:24:48,930
I was always serious
when it came to you, Se Ri.

360
00:24:50,790 --> 00:24:53,500
Why would you care about
a troublemaker like me?

361
00:24:57,300 --> 00:25:00,240
Everyone blooms
if they're given enough love.

362
00:25:01,670 --> 00:25:03,170
You may feel like a weed,

363
00:25:03,940 --> 00:25:07,140
but things change if someone
waters you and cares for you.

364
00:25:08,210 --> 00:25:09,280
Then...

365
00:25:10,210 --> 00:25:11,980
can I change too?

366
00:25:14,320 --> 00:25:15,320
Of course you can.

367
00:25:16,320 --> 00:25:17,650
I'll help you.

368
00:25:25,260 --> 00:25:26,330
Are you crying?

369
00:25:28,700 --> 00:25:29,930
Why would I cry?

370
00:25:30,930 --> 00:25:32,470
I'm not a child.

371
00:25:36,770 --> 00:25:38,070
I'll call you back.

372
00:25:41,010 --> 00:25:42,280
Don't come to the office again.

373
00:25:43,110 --> 00:25:45,880
I won't put up with you
bringing that woman a packed lunch.

374
00:25:46,280 --> 00:25:48,890
Shouldn't you worry
and ask how I feel first?

375
00:25:49,690 --> 00:25:51,860
I was humiliated in public.

376
00:25:51,860 --> 00:25:53,890
Don't you care what it did to my ego?

377
00:25:54,120 --> 00:25:55,660
Don't act like you're in the right.

378
00:25:56,260 --> 00:25:58,930
- If you visit that woman again...
- Stop calling her that!

379
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:01,330
She's a good person.

380
00:26:01,460 --> 00:26:03,130
She's much nicer than you.

381
00:26:19,550 --> 00:26:20,580
Where's Director Moon?

382
00:26:21,150 --> 00:26:22,250
He'll be here soon.

383
00:26:22,890 --> 00:26:24,450
Tell him to come straight to my office.

384
00:26:37,970 --> 00:26:39,300
Why do you have this?

385
00:26:42,510 --> 00:26:43,810
Why do you have it?

386
00:26:44,670 --> 00:26:46,240
Ask the chairman.

387
00:26:46,910 --> 00:26:48,350
He gave it to you?

388
00:26:49,480 --> 00:26:51,050
Would I have stolen it?

389
00:26:54,250 --> 00:26:55,290
Give it to me.

390
00:26:55,290 --> 00:26:57,550
- What are you doing? Let go.
- Give it to me!

391
00:26:57,890 --> 00:26:58,920
- Stop.
- Give it to me!

392
00:26:58,920 --> 00:26:59,990
- Ms. Min.
- Let go of me!

393
00:26:59,990 --> 00:27:01,260
Stop it!

394
00:27:01,260 --> 00:27:02,760
- What's going on here?
- Let go!

395
00:27:06,430 --> 00:27:07,430
Calm down.

396
00:27:09,300 --> 00:27:10,700
What was that about?

397
00:27:11,370 --> 00:27:13,370
It's none of your business,
so stay out of it.

398
00:27:14,240 --> 00:27:17,010
No. I can't do that.

399
00:27:17,070 --> 00:27:18,580
You can back off.

400
00:27:18,780 --> 00:27:20,910
Aren't you the one who should back off?

401
00:27:20,940 --> 00:27:22,580
Stay out of this woman's business!

402
00:27:22,580 --> 00:27:24,780
I will get involved
because it involves her!

403
00:27:44,230 --> 00:27:47,940
(The Woman Who Swallowed the Sun)

404
00:27:59,850 --> 00:28:01,320
What happens now?

405
00:28:01,320 --> 00:28:02,820
Will the chairman marry her?

406
00:28:02,820 --> 00:28:04,490
We can't allow such a tragedy.

407
00:28:04,490 --> 00:28:06,490
I won't leave that woman alone.

408
00:28:06,490 --> 00:28:09,090
They could be having a private tea party,

409
00:28:09,090 --> 00:28:10,530
acting like lovers.

410
00:28:10,530 --> 00:28:12,930
You don't want me to notice?
Shall I stay out of it?

411
00:28:12,930 --> 00:28:14,330
What's in there?

412
00:28:14,330 --> 00:28:15,600
Leverage on Min Doo Sik.

413
00:28:15,600 --> 00:28:17,700
A collar that, when tightened,
will take him straight to his death.

414
00:28:17,830 --> 00:28:20,640
Who cares about the safe?
We can just steal it.

415
